The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, March 15, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, March 14: NIIT has called an extra-ordinary general meeting of shareholders on March 24 to get their approval for spinning off its software business and restructuring of the equity. It has proposed spinning of the software solutions business into a separate entity to be called NIIT Technologies Ltd, said Sanjiv Kataria, executive vice-president. Post restructuring, the firms equity base would rise to Rs 57 crore from Rs 38 crore at present.																								 New Delhi, March 14: Reliance Infocomm has got a letter of intent for offering CDMA-based mobile services in Jammu and Kashmir. With this Reliances reach virtually extends across the country.																								 New Delhi, March 14: The decks were cleared for production at Essar Oils refinery as the company told lenders it would not use Ratna oilfields to repay loans.																								 Mumbai, March 14: Videsh Sanchar Nigam has set up a wholly-owned unit in Singapore, VSNL Singapore Pte Ltd.
